cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM 

The paper deals with computer vision problems such as wide-baseline matching and view synthesis, which are commonly studied in the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The use of detectors and algorithms to solve these problems involves optimization and machine learning techniques, which are also relevant to the cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The paper also discusses experimental results and comparisons with state-of-the-art methods, which are typical of the cs.GR (Graphics) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image processing and manipulation, which is relevant to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
